title.narrative: YOUTH INNOVATION LAB

description.narrative: Youth Innovation Lab functional and able to foster innovative solutions for youth affected by poverty, adversity and exclusion, which contributes to Adolescent Empowerment, Adolescent Empowerment (Covid), Economic And Social Policy General, Human Rights Institutions, Other Cross-Sectoral Programme Areas, Skills Development, Social Protection. UNICEF aims to achieve this through Fostering Innovation And Use Of New Technologies, Systems Strengthening And Institution Building. This contributes to the following Country Programme result: Girls and boys, especially those affected by poverty, adversity and exclusion, progressively utilise quality, inclusive and efficient education system reinforced by policies, programmes and services for empowerment and participation, by 2022.

title.narrative: Youth Innovation Lab functional and able to foster innovative solutions for youth affected by poverty, adversity and exclusion

description.narrative: Adolescent girls and boys increasingly benefited from skills-building programmes aimed at promoting 21st century skills, provided by the UNICEF-supported Youth Innovation Lab. Vulnerable adolescents such as those in residential care, with behavioral problems, in conflict with the law and Roma boys and girls, acquired socio-emotional skills through non-formal education. Through the UN regional joint programme "Dialogue for the Future", youth and adolescents had the opportunity to learn from and work with youth and adolescents from neighboring countries. | Status:On-track | As-of Date:20/12/2019
